# Track only the bundled, no-credential DADLs and the README — everything else
# in this directory is the user's own files and stays untracked, so a pull or
# branch switch never disturbs the user's local DADLs.
#
# This is a temporary solution. The proper fix is to split bundled and
# user-managed DADLs into separate directories (see CHANGELOG / issue tracker).
*
!.gitignore
!README.md
!hackernews.dadl
!algolia-hn-search.dadl
